me <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Elinor Spalding was born in 1211, in Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Ralph Spalding, was 32 and her mother, Mrs Ralph Spalding, was 22. She married Roger Copledike in 1225, in Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"1211–":"1211–Surnud","1211–Female":"1211–Surnud","1209–1235":"1209–1235","1235–1273":"1235–1273","1180–Male":"1180–Surnud","1189–Female":"1189–Surnud","1225":"1225","1235":"1235","1211":"1211","1189":"1189","12350000":"1235","1273":"1273","1209":"1209","1180":"1180","Lincolnshire,England":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Copledike, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Of,, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1211–":"1211–Kuollut","1211–Female":"1211–Kuollut","1209–1235":"1209–1235","1235–1273":"1235–1273","1180–Male":"1180–Kuollut","1189–Female":"1189–Kuollut","1225":"1225","1235":"1235","1211":"1211","1189":"1189","12350000":"1235","1273":"1273","1209":"1209","1180":"1180","Lincolnshire,England":"Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Copledike, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Of,, Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1211–":"1211–Décédée","1211–Female":"1211–Décédée","1209–1235":"1209–1235","1235–1273":"1235–1273","1180–Male":"1180–Décédé","1189–Female":"1189–Décédée","1225":"1225","1235":"1235","1211":"1211","1189":"1189","1